injury.description: Aug 25: Floyd is considered day-to-day after sustaining a knee injury in Friday's preseason game against the Raiders, Cam Inman of The San Jose Mercury News reports.
Aug 16: Banks broke his pinkie finger Thursday and had to undergo surgery, but head coach Kyle Shanahan says the hope is that he'll be ready for Week 1, Nick Wagoner of ESPN.com reports.
Aug 26: Williams plans to continue his holdout until his contract is addressed, putting his Week 1 availability into question, Jeremy Fowler of ESPN.com reports.
Aug 18: Jennings didn't play in Sunday's 16-10 preseason win over the Saints due to an oblique injury, Matt Maiocco of NBC Sports Bay Area reports.
Aug 15: McCaffrey (calf) increased his activity level on the side field at practice Thursday and seems to be getting closer to a return, Nick Wagoner of ESPN.com reports.
Aug 25: Gross-Matos is considered week-to-week after injuring his knee in Friday's preseason game against Las Vegas, Cam Inman of The San Jose Mercury News reports.
Aug 7: Warner was held out of Wednesday's practice due to foot irritation, Nick Wagoner of ESPN.com reports.
Aug 28: Guerendo tweaked his groin Monday and won't practice this week, Cam Inman of The San Jose Mercury News reports.
Aug 25: Winters will have an MRI this week to determine the severity of his ankle injury, Lindsey Pallares of the 49ers' official site reports.
Aug 20: Burford (hand) is expected to return to participate in individual drills at practice this week, Nick Wagoner of ESPN.com reports.
Aug 26: Pearsall (shoulder) returned to practice Monday in a non-contact jersey, Nick Wagoner of ESPN.com reports.
